description:
- Added accidentally removed intro for left rhythm guitar;
- Empty 6th string during lead guitar intro rings now longer;
- Tempo fix from 81 to 80 as on the album version seems to be slower like that;
- Initial noise from the left rhythm guitar now lasts longer and is marked as natural harmonics to sound closer to the studio version;
- Right rhythm guitar obtained marked upstrokes in "chug-ding" pre-chorus section;

Changed:
- Lead guitar measures 2-31: arpeggio intro sounds fatter on the album so it needs to be played in higher positions. Also it seems to be played live this way;
- Lead guitar measures 72-103, 128-159: lead riff but as above - fatter;
- Rhythm guitar left and right measuers 48-71, 112-127: pre-chorus chords made a little more playable, as played on live performances;
- Rhythm guitar left measures 72-103, 128-143: chorus riff made fatter by playing on one string;

Most of the changes are inspired by watching live performances and listening to the timbre of the album version to find a proper timbre. If my changes seem to be too "live", it would be possible to make a separate live version which is also played a little faster like about 90 bpm.
